L6­1.3 

Divisibility facts


1.  a|b ⇒ a|bc for all c 
2.  a|b and b|c ⇒ a|c 
3.  a|b and a|c ⇒a|sb+tc for all s,t

i.e., a divides every linear 
combination of b and c 

4.  for all c ≠0,  a|b ⇔ac|bc 
