L6­1.4 

Proof of “a|b and b|c ⇒ a|c’’


∃ k1, k2  such that 
ak1  = b  and  bk2  = c 

⋅k2  = c 
so  ak1 
⋅k2  gives ak’ = c 
letting k’=k1 
⇒ a|c 

