L6­1.5 

Division Theorem

For all n, for all d>0,

there is a unique  q,r such that

n  = qd + r


where 0 ≤r < d 

(r= n rem d) 

Example:  n = 6042  d= 10

6042 = 604 ⋅10 + 2

